Predatory mites, the use of which is recommended for the biological control of phytophagous mites, thrips, and whiteflies, both in greenhouses and outdoors, will continue to gain importance in the future, as biological control represents an increasingly widespread alternative to chemical control of plant pests (

; 

). With the planned large reduction in the use of pesticides in Europe already in the near future (EIP-AGRI, 2022), the most likely use of biological control agents will be among the most common measures to maintain the abundance of harmful organisms below the harmful threshold.
